**[1862, 02-25] Ms.B.1.6.9.10**

May Jr. to RDW. 8pp. {Bulk in {u}BAA{/u}.} May refers to the Confederacy
as “the rebels.” “We were both surprised and disappointed to see how
quickly (how seemingly spontaneously) and how furiously the flame of
war-feeling against the country burst forth in England. It was a
revelation of an unexpected fact. … Our nation and government were
treated, in the Mason and Slidell case, as tho’ an international insult
to England had been planned and executed.”


